The paper deals with mathematical models of self-assembling tiles, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the impacts of dimensionality and directedness on intrinsic universality, which are concepts related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also presents results related to simulation and implementation, which are topics related to scientific computing (cs.SC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
